    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect HARQ configuration handling in nr_pdsch_ptrs_processing\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_pdsch_ptrs_processing` function in the NR UE channel estimation module had a logic flaw that could cause incorrect PTRS processing when both HARQ processes were present. The function would overwrite configuration variables for dlsch[0] with those from dlsch[1], even when dlsch[1] was not active, leading to incorrect phase error estimation and compensation.\n\nThis manifested as degraded PDSCH performance when PTRS was enabled, particularly in scenarios with multiple active HARQ processes. Users reported unexpected behavior when calling `nr_pdsch_ptrs_processing()` where the function would not process PTRS correctly due to using configuration from the wrong HARQ process.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_UE_ESTIMATION/nr_dl_channel_estimation.c`: Fixed logic flaw in HARQ process configuration handling.\n  - Added proper null pointer checks for both dlsch0_harq and dlsch1_harq\n  - Changed from sequential if statements to if/else if to prevent configuration overwrites\n  - Added early return when no active HARQ process is found\n  - Updated processing logic to use the correctly configured active HARQ process\n\n"
}